From: OCR-to-Anki project
Subject: Fix CL_INVALID_WORK_GROUP_SIZE on Intel iGPUs (max 256)

The kernel_geglu dispatch hardcodes local_work_size to 512, which exceeds
the max work group size (256) on Intel UHD Graphics (CML GT2 / Gen9).
This causes CL_INVALID_WORK_GROUP_SIZE (-54) during warmup.

Fix: clamp nth to backend_ctx->max_workgroup_size.

Upstream bug: should be filed at https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp

--- a/ggml/src/ggml-opencl/ggml-opencl.cpp
+++ b/ggml/src/ggml-opencl/ggml-opencl.cpp
@@ -11230,6 +11230,9 @@
 
     const size_t nrows = ggml_nrows(src0);
     size_t nth = 512;
+    if (nth > backend_ctx->max_workgroup_size) {
+        nth = backend_ctx->max_workgroup_size;
+    }
     size_t global_work_size[] = {nrows*nth, 1, 1};
     size_t local_work_size[] = {nth, 1, 1};
